This paper focuses on automated test case generation, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms (such as DynaMOSA) in the test case generation process, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a set of performance proxies to measure runtime and memory usage, which could be considered a form of machine learning (cs.LG) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) depending on the specific implementation.
